# Preventing Unnecessary Re-renders in React

You have several options depending on your situation:

## 1. **`React.memo()` - For Functional Components**

Wrap your component to skip re-renders when props haven't changed:

```jsx
const MyComponent = React.memo(({ name, age }) => {
  return <div>{name} - {age}</div>;
});
```

This does a **shallow comparison** of props by default.

## 2. **Custom Comparison with `memo`**

For deeper prop comparisons:

```jsx
const MyComponent = React.memo(
  ({ user }) => <div>{user.name}</div>,
  (prevProps, nextProps) => {
    // Return true if props are equal (skip re-render)
    // Return false to re-render
    return prevProps.user.id === nextProps.user.id;
  }
);
```

## 3. **`useMemo()` - Memoize Expensive Calculations**

If the parent is creating new objects/arrays each render:

```jsx
function Parent() {
  // ❌ Creates new object every render
  // const config = { name: 'John' };

  // ✅ Only recreates when dependencies change
  const config = useMemo(() => ({ name: 'John' }), []);

  return <Child config={config} />;
}
```

## 4. **`useCallback()` - Memoize Functions**

Prevent new function references:

```jsx
function Parent() {
  // ✅ Function reference stays the same between renders
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    console.log('clicked');
  }, []); // dependencies array

  return <Child onClick={handleClick} />;
}
```

## 5. **Class Components - `PureComponent` or `shouldComponentUpdate()`**

```jsx
class MyComponent extends React.PureComponent {
  // Automatically does shallow prop/state comparison
  render() {
    return <div>{this.props.name}</div>;
  }
}
```

Or custom logic:

```jsx
shouldComponentUpdate(nextProps, nextState) {
  return nextProps.id !== this.props.id;
}
```

## Quick Comparison

| Solution | Use Case |
|----------|----------|
| `React.memo()` | Simple prop comparison |
| `useMemo()` | Parent creates new objects/arrays |
| `useCallback()` | Parent passes function props |
| `PureComponent` | Class components |

**Pro tip:** Use React DevTools Profiler to identify unnecessary re-renders first!

# Integrating Claude into Next.js: Simplest Approach

The easiest path is **Anthropic's SDK + API Routes**, which handles streaming natively:

## 1. Install & Configure

```bash
npm install @anthropic-ai/sdk
```

Create `.env.local`:
```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

## 2. Create an API Route for Streaming

`app/api/ask/route.ts`:
```typescript
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";

const anthropic = new Anthropic({
  apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
});

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  const { question, context } = await request.json();

  const stream = await anthropic.messages.create({
    model: "claude-opus-4-6",
    max_tokens: 1024,
    system: `You are a helpful assistant analyzing user data. 
Context about the user's data: ${context}`,
    messages: [
      {
        role: "user",
        content: question,
      },
    ],
    stream: true,
  });

  // Convert Anthropic stream to ReadableStream for Next.js
  const readableStream = new ReadableStream({
    async start(controller) {
      for await (const event of stream) {
        if (
          event.type === "content_block_delta" &&
          event.delta.type === "text_delta"
        ) {
          controller.enqueue(
            new TextEncoder().encode(event.delta.text)
          );
        }
      }
      controller.close();
    },
  });

  return new NextResponse(readableStream, {
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "text/event-stream",
      "Cache-Control": "no-cache",
    },
  });
}
```

## 3. Client Component for Streaming UI

`components/AskAboutData.tsx`:
```typescript
"use client";

import { useState } from "react";

export function AskAboutData() {
  const [question, setQuestion] = useState("");
  const [response, setResponse] = useState("");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleAsk = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    setResponse("");

    try {
      const res = await fetch("/api/ask", {
        method: "POST",
        body: JSON.stringify({
          question,
          context: "User has 500 transactions, avg $250 each", // Replace with real data
        }),
      });

      const reader = res.body?.getReader();
      const decoder = new TextDecoder();

      while (reader) {
        const { done, value } = await reader.read();
        if (done) break;
        setResponse((prev) => prev + decoder.decode(value, { stream: true }));
      }
    } catch (error) {
      setResponse("Error: " + String(error));
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="space-y-4">
      <textarea
        value={question}
        onChange={(e) => setQuestion(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Ask about your data..."
        className="w-full p-2 border rounded"
      />
      <button
        onClick={handleAsk}
        disabled={loading}
        className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded disabled:opacity-50"
      >
        {loading ? "Thinking..." : "Ask"}
      </button>
      {response && (
        <div className="p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded whitespace-pre-wrap">
          {response}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```

